article.headline: Tulane 78, New Orleans 64
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Chris Moore had five 3-pointers and scored 20 points to lead Tulane to a 78-64 win over New Orleans on Tuesday night. Moore hit 6-of-9 shots and made 5-of-6 3-pointers. He also grabbed five rebounds for Tulane (1-1). Donnie Smith had 12 points and David Gomez 11 as the Green Wave hit 51.9 percent of its field goals for the game. Bo McCalebb led New Orleans (1-3) with 27 points and 13 rebounds. He made 12-of-30 shots but was 0-of-3 from the 3-point range. Jamie McNeilly added 19 points and Jacob Manning 8. Tulane led 35-30 at the halftime and outscored New Orleans 43-34 in the second half. New Orleans was kept to 36.7 percent shooting for the game and missed 5 of its 23 3-point attempts. New Orleans outrebounded Tulane 42-36 but turned the ball over 17 times compared to Tulane's 12. Tulane also had 18 assists to New Orleans' 9.
